For this project, I used Canva to design a one-page visual resource on digital literacy. Since I’m still new to designing, Canva made the process much easier with its simple interface and templates. In my visual, I mainly focused on explaining what digital literacy is, some useful digital tools that students can use in their daily studies, and basic safe internet practices. I described digital literacy as the ability to use technology in a smart and responsible way. I also added examples of tools that can help in studying and managing work, along with simple safety tips like not sharing personal information and being careful about which websites we trust.
One thing I found slightly difficult was balancing the content and design, because I didn’t want the page to look too crowded. At the same time, I enjoyed experimenting with different layouts and colors to make it look more attractive. Overall, this project helped me understand the importance of digital literacy and also improved my confidence in creating simple designs.
